<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[5] He also notes that the thing that the depo=
sit franchise is a hedge *for* is the *mortgage business*. He describes thi=
s as =E2=80=9Cthe mortgage industrial complex,=E2=80=9D the process in mode=
rn US finance by which mortgages get their credit risk guaranteed by govern=
ment-sponsored entities and are then packaged into mortgage-backed securiti=
es that are sold to banks, who bear the interest-rate risk. This is a compl=
icated roundabout version of a very traditional banking business: In =E2=80=
=9CIt=E2=80=99s a Wonderful Life,=E2=80=9D the bank takes deposits and uses=
